              "name": "subtitle",
              "fill": "$--text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The per-frame duration editing control for PRD 193 (M4) - sibling to the 187 Frame Ruler spec. Edits the active frame's display time in milliseconds, reusing the ruler's frame selection (click a frame, edit its duration). An active-frame-only editor lives in the panel's top-left corner, aligned with the ruler. Tokens-only; Light + Dark via theming. This is NOT the reserved transport strip (that strip is global playback - out of scope).",
