        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "T6KzP",
          "name": "Desktop expanded (Dark)",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 20,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "W3zKp",
              "name": "sec-title",
              "fill": "$--text-primary",
              "content": "§2 Desktop - expanded (Dark)",
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 22,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "vQ7ni",
              "name": "sec-desc",
              "fill": "$--text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The same panel and corner editor in Dark mode (theme tokens only). The input chip, the ms unit, and the read-only fps helper all read against the dark surface; the active column (3) and the corner stay legible. No color is hard-coded - every value is a --ds-* token resolved per theme.",
