              "name": "sec-desc",
              "fill": "$--text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "A bounce: the previous Frame's ball tinted toward $--onion-prev, the next Frame's toward $--onion-next, the Active Frame's committed art untouched and always on top. Recipe per ghost: composite_at(neighbor) → ~60% blend toward the tint token → drawn at ~40% alpha, nearest-neighbor, between the Reference underlay and the Active composite. Transparent ghost pixels stay transparent — the checkerboard shows through. Swatches below are computed with the real formula, so this mock is an honest preview.",
